properties.Name: ChannelAggregateProductCancellations
properties.Description:
The total Product cancellations expressed in terms of unit quantity and cancellations valuation for the associated timestamp.

Cancellations represent the canceling of an order after it has been booked and billed.   This represents the most serious condition of all to a business in which real revenue has been lost after the hard sales work has been done.
In this case cancellations are summarized for a product across all customers.

Columns.Name: ChannelId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Channel.

Columns.Name: ProductId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Product.

Columns.Name: Timestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the associated information is reported, recorded or effective as-of.

Columns.Name: TotalCancelledProductUnitsQuantity
Columns.Description: The total quantity of Product cancelled for the associated date.

Columns.Name: TotalCancelledProductUnitsValuationAmount
Columns.Description: The total valuation of Product cancelled during the associated period and valued at actual invoiced price.

Columns.Name: IsoCurrencyCode
Columns.Description:
The ISO 4217 currency code.

Ex:
Currency Code = AED
Currency Name = Dirham
Country Name = United Arab Emirates
